<collectingCountry box="[234,360,332,356]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="121.[151,1437,151,392]" box="[199,1327,367,392]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">
Etymology. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[563,622,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erato">
<emphasis box="[563,622,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">erato</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is chosen in honor of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[871,935,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erato">Erato</taxonomicName>
, the Muse of lyric and love-poetry.
</paragraph>
